cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and discourse parsing. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a joint syntacto-discourse parser that uses machine learning techniques. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with automated parsing of natural language text. 
4. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a possible category as discourse parsing can be useful in information retrieval tasks. 
5. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a neural network-based approach for joint syntacto-discourse parsing.
